data.content:
Here's the full `Program.cs`:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Alice", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase,
    WriteIndented = true
};

Console.WriteLine(JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options));

public record Person(string name, int age);
```

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` — new in .NET 11. It joins the existing built-in policies (`CamelCase`, `SnakeCaseLower`, `SnakeCaseUpper`, `KebabCaseLower`, `KebabCaseUpper`) so you don't need a custom implementation. It converts the lowercase record parameter names (`name`, `age`) to PascalCase (`Name`, `Age`) in the JSON output.
